        <sect2 xml:id="view-panels" xreflabel="View Panels">
            <title>View Panels</title>
            <para>The dividers between panels can be dragged to change the size of any of the
                panels. &productshort; remembers the position of the dividers, so the next time
                starts it uses the positions of the dividers from the last time the program was
                used.</para>

            <para>If a single dive is selected in the *Dive List*, the dive location, detailed
                information and profile of the _selected dive_ are shown in the respective panels.
                If several dives are selected, the last highlighted dive is the _selected dive_, but
                summary data of all _highlighted dives_ is shown in the *Stats* tab of the *Info*
                panel (maximum, minimum and average depths, durations, water temperatures and SAC;
                total time and number of dives selected).</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guilabel>Dive List</guilabel> (bottom left)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows the dives in the user's dive log. Dives in the list can be
                            selected by clicking on a record. The selected record is highlighted. In
                            adding to selection by mouse click, the <keycap>UP</keycap> and
                                <keycap>DOWN</keycap> keys on the keyboard can also be used to
                            change selection. Multiple dive records can be selected by holding down
                            the <keycap>CTRL</keycap> key and clicking additional records.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guilabel>Dive Map</guilabel> (bottom right)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows the dive site location of the record selected in the
                                <guilabel>Dive List</guilabel>. The dive location is displayed
                            centered on a world map and marked by a dive flag. The map scale can be
                            increased or decreased.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guilabel>Dive Info</guilabel> (top left)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows more detailed information on the dive selected in the
                                <guilabel>Dive List</guilabel>, including some statistics for the
                            selected dive or for all highlighted dive(s).</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guilabel>Dive Profile</guilabel> (top right)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Shows a graphical dive profile of the selected dive in the
                                <guilabel>Dive List</guilabel>. You can zoom into the dive profile
                            for a more detailed view.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
